I want to to report an bug/incident:  At the beginning the application recognised automatically whenever I was riding a bike, but since some time ago it just does not and I have not changed my smartphone. Therefore I kindly ask you to investigate this issue.  Things I like:  - It evaluates your progess and phisical status based on the intensity of your activity apart from the time, which is very nice. - It is based on the WHO recommendations.  Things I don't like:  - The integration with the Mi Fit application is rather poor and it does not provide the possibility to sync with other wearables that are not Wear OS, at least, it is not possible with the Mi Band. - It does not detect when you use the stairs (I am climbing 16 floors twice per day). - The integration with the objectives of Google Calendar only works fine if you introduce the activity in the Google Fit app, then, the Calendar objective will update, but not the other way around. Further work needs to be done here.  Regards, Pablo Msa
